INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2011-11-17 23:14:45','2011-11-17 23:14:45','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2011-11-28 05:06:08','2011-11-28 05:06:08','',0,'http://blog.loc/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2011-11-17 23:14:45','2011-11-17 23:14:45','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://blog.loc/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','trash','open','open','','sample-page','','','2011-11-28 05:07:49','2011-11-28 05:07:49','',0,'http://blog.loc/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(31,1,'2011-11-28 22:42:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2011-11-28 22:42:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://blog.loc/?p=31',0,'post','',0),(4,1,'2011-11-18 04:01:21','2011-11-18 04:01:21','About a year ago, I woke up on a Saturday morning really wanting to volunteer. I spent some time in high school volunteering, but never a significant amount. I just couldn’t find a place that wanted me when I wanted them. This particular morning, I experienced the same problem. I googled volunteering and found a few websites that offered to put me in touch with a volunteer coordinator. I created the accounts and sent out the emails. No immediate responses. So I asked my roommate if he knew where to volunteer and he didn’t. I decided to walk down the hall of my dorm. Surely one of my fellow honors students would tell me where I could go. No luck. Everyone went through their church or fraternity or student organization. The times were set for them. All I wanted to do help my community for an afternoon but I struggled to figure out how.\r\n\r\nInstead of trying harder to find a place to volunteer, I wondered if others had the same problem. If I couldn’t find a place to volunteer for a few hours on a Saturday morning, who else couldn’t? Was there a need for a website that allowed volunteers to discover opportunities based on interests and availability? I ran a survey and out of the 200 responses, over half said they often couldn’t figure out where to volunteer. It really shouldn’t be that hard.\r\n\r\nTurns out I can’t write a line of code. I took a computer science class in high school and got a 1 on the AP test. It was really hard. I decided to apply for 3DayStartup, an entrepreneurship weekend where 40 students from 15 disciplines launch a series of technology companies. There, I met Mike who realized that I was on to something. Hence, 2HourCommitment was born.\r\n\r\nWe knew that students had difficulty volunteering, but wondered whether non-profits faced difficulty as well. They did. Some of the organizations we talked to needed management tools to keep track of their volunteers while others just needed help recruiting. We decided to solve both.','Our Story','','publish','open','open','','our-story','','','2011-11-18 04:01:21','2011-11-18 04:01:21','',0,'http://blog.loc/?p=4',0,'post','',0),(5,1,'2011-11-18 04:00:41','2011-11-18 04:00:41','','Our Story','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision','','','2011-11-18 04:00:41','20